{
  "texts": [
    "In contrast, AC adopts a broad range of harmful categories based on Do-Not-Answer dataset [14] (hereinafter referred to as DNA) which was originally developed for English, providing one of the most comprehensive safety categories for LLM output.",
    "Unlike DNA which uses GPT-4 to generate the questions in the dataset, we collected our questions manually from our contracted annotators.",
    "This ensures that the questions are natural, realistic and free of usage restrictions, unlike those in DNA which tend to be templatic, abstract and unnatural and are bound by the usage terms of GPT-4.",
    "Another difference from DNA is that our dataset includes reference answers paired with the questions so as to serve as an instruction data for fine-tuning LLMs.",
    "We used AC for fine-tuning LLM-jp-13B-v2.0, a Japanese LLM developed by LLM-jpfoot_2, and found that the harmful answer rate of the model was significantly reduced without compromising the usefulness of answers to general questions."
  ]
}